{"description":"As per type resolution for numerical type {{int}} is considered a subtype of {{double}} but casting an int to a double is legit  : \n\n{code}\nint a \u003d 2;\nint b \u003d 3;\ndouble d \u003d (double)a/(double)b; \n{code}\n\nThe only issue to raise on numerical cast is when type is the same : \n{code}\nint a \u003d 0;\nint b \u003d (int) a; //unecessary cast\n{code}","component":"SonarJava","component_version":"2.7"}